content.text:
I now have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Here is the detailed implementation plan.

---

## Implementation Plan: Inline Draft Note Creation Flow

### Overview

Replace the modal-based note creation with an inline "draft note" that renders directly on the Konva canvas, accompanied by a floating design panel in the DOM (between the toolbar and the canvas). The draft note is draggable, updates live as the user types/styles, and is finalized with a "Place Note" button.

---

### Step 1: Replace `noteModal` State with `draftNote` State

**File:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\freedomWall\FreedomWallPage.jsx`

**Current state (line 364):**
```js
const [noteModal, setNoteModal] = useState(null);
```

**Change to:**
```js
const [draftNote, setDraftNote] = useState(null);
```

The `draftNote` object shape remains the same as `noteModal`:
```js
{
    x: 0.45,        // normalized 0-1
    y: 0.45,        // normalized 0-1
    text: "",
    fontFamily: "Arial",
    fontStyle: "normal",
    fontColor: "#1f2937",
    bgColor: "#fff4a8",
    fontSize: 16
}
```

The key difference: `text` starts as empty string `""` instead of `"New note"`, since the user will type into the panel. Also add a note that the default position should be centered around the click point rather than using the raw click coordinate as top-left (subtract half the note width/height in normalized coordinates).

---

### Step 2: Update `handlePlaceItem` to Set `draftNote` Instead of `noteModal`

**File:** `FreedomWallPage.jsx`, lines 726-737

Change the `activeTool === "note"` branch inside `handlePlaceItem`:

```js
if (activeTool === "note") {
    setDraftNote({
        x: pointer.x,
        y: pointer.y,
        text: "",
        fontFamily: "Arial",
        fontStyle: "normal",
        fontColor: "#1f2937",
        bgColor: "#fff4a8",
        fontSize: 16
    });
}
```

Also add a guard: if `draftNote` is already set when the user clicks canvas with note tool, ignore the click (prevent creating a second draft while one is active). Add at the top of the `activeTool === "note"` block:

```js
if (activeTool === "note") {
    if (draftNote) return; // already drafting
    // ... set draft
}
```

---

### Step 3: Cancel Draft on Tool Switch

**File:** `FreedomWallPage.jsx`

Add a `useEffect` that clears the draft when the active tool changes away from "note":

```js
useEffect(() => {
    if (activeTool !== "note") {
        setDraftNote(null);
    }
}, [activeTool]);
```

This ensures switching tools automatically discards any in-progress draft.

---

### Step 4: Render Draft Note on the Konva Canvas

**File:** `FreedomWallPage.jsx`, inside the items `<Layer>` (after the `sortedItems.map(...)` block, around line 1256)

Add a conditional `NoteNode` for the draft, rendered after all other items so it appears on top. The draft needs a distinct visual indicator -- use a dashed border. Modify the `NoteNode` component to accept an optional `isDraft` prop.

**Draft note rendering (after the doodle draft lines, around line 1268):**
```jsx
{draftNote && (
    <NoteNode
        item={{
            payload: {
                ...draftNote,
                width: 0.26,
                height: 0.2,
                rotation: 0
            }
        }}
        stageWidth={stageWidth}
        stageHeight={stageHeight}
        canEdit={true}
        isSelected={false}
        isDraft={true}
        onSelect={() => {}}
        onDragEnd={(event) => {
            const node = event?.target;
            if (!node) return;
            setDraftNote((prev) => ({
                ...prev,
                x: clamp(node.x() / stageWidth, 0, 1),
                y: clamp(node.y() / stageHeight, 0, 1)
            }));
        }}
    />
)}
```

**Modify `NoteNode` component (line 216)** to accept `isDraft` prop and render a dashed selection border when `isDraft` is true:

```jsx
const NoteNode = ({item, stageWidth, stageHeight, canEdit, onSelect, onDragEnd, isSelected, isDraft = false}) => {
```

Change the stroke on the main note body shape (line 265):
```js
stroke={isDraft ? "#a21caf" : isSelected ? "#a21caf" : "rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"}
strokeWidth={isDraft ? 2 : isSelected ? 2 : 0.5}
dash={isDraft ? [8, 4] : undefined}
```

This gives the draft note a dashed purple border so users see it is a preview/draft.

---

### Step 5: Replace the Modal JSX with an Inline Design Panel

**File:** `FreedomWallPage.jsx`, lines 1017-1083 (the `noteModal &&` block)

Remove the entire `fw-note-modal-overlay` / `fw-note-modal` block. Replace it with an inline panel that renders **between the toolbar and the canvas** (right after the toolbar's closing `</div>` on line 1015, before the `selectedNote && selectedItemCanEdit` block on line 1085).

**New JSX:**
```jsx
{draftNote && (
    <div className="fw-draft-note-panel">
        <div className="fw-draft-note-panel-header">
            <h4>Design Your Note</h4>
            <span className="fw-draft-char-count">
                {draftNote.text.length}/200
            </span>
        </div>

        <textarea
            className="fw-draft-note-textarea"
            value={draftNote.text}
            onChange={(e) => setDraftNote((prev) => ({
                ...prev,
                text: e.target.value.slice(0, 200)
            }))}
            maxLength={200}
            placeholder="Type your note..."
            autoFocus
        />

        <div className="fw-draft-note-controls">
            <div className="fw-draft-note-row">
                <label>Font</label>
                <select
                    value={draftNote.fontFamily}
                    onChange={(e) => setDraftNote((prev) => ({...prev, fontFamily: e.target.value}))}
                >
                    {NOTE_FONT_OPTIONS.map((fontName) => (
                        <option key={fontName} value={fontName}>{fontName}</option>
                    ))}
                </select>
            </div>

            <div className="fw-draft-note-row">
                <label>Style</label>
                <select
                    value={draftNote.fontStyle}
                    onChange={(e) => setDraftNote((prev) => ({...prev, fontStyle: e.target.value}))}
                >
                    {NOTE_STYLE_OPTIONS.map((styleName) => (
                        <option key={styleName} value={styleName}>{styleName}</option>
                    ))}
                </select>
            </div>

            <div className="fw-draft-note-row">
                <label>Font color</label>
                <input
                    type="color"
                    value={draftNote.fontColor}
                    onChange={(e) => setDraftNote((prev) => ({...prev, fontColor: e.target.value}))}
                />
            </div>

            <div className="fw-draft-note-row">
                <label>Note color</label>
                <input
                    type="color"
                    value={draftNote.bgColor}
                    onChange={(e) => setDraftNote((prev) => ({...prev, bgColor: e.target.value}))}
                />
            </div>

            <div className="fw-draft-note-row">
                <label>Size ({draftNote.fontSize}px)</label>
                <input
                    type="range"
                    min={10}
                    max={64}
                    step={1}
                    value={draftNote.fontSize}
                    onChange={(e) => setDraftNote((prev) => ({...prev, fontSize: Number(e.target.value)}))}
                />
            </div>
        </div>

        <div className="fw-draft-note-actions">
            <button
                type="button"
                className="fw-apply-btn"
                onClick={handleDraftNoteSave}
                disabled={!draftNote.text.trim()}
            >
                Place Note
            </button>
            <button
                type="button"
                className="fw-delete-btn"
                onClick={() => setDraftNote(null)}
            >
                Cancel
            </button>
        </div>
    </div>
)}
